data.meta_description: Pampanga - Wiki - Free download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. Pampanga is a province in the Philippines located in Central Luzon. It has a population of over 2 million people and was the first province established by the Spanish in 1571. Pampanga played an important role in the Philippines' struggle for independence, revolting against Spain and aiding guerilla fighters against the Japanese during World War 2. It is known as the culinary capital of the Philippines and is famous for its food.
